      "name": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions",
      "description": "Monte Carlo sampling (N=500) performed over inlet velocity, viscosity, and power-law hemolysis model coefficients. 95th-percentile prediction interval spans factor of 2.1 around median hemolysis index. A screening sensitivity ranking was conducted informally during UQ post-processing to identify dominant contributors; power-law exponent identified as primary driver. No structured SensitivityAnalysis node was created from this screening exercise."
    }
